  "body": "### Description\n\nOIDC provides a means to report errors to the callback endpoint, but the current OIDC code should not invoke the user endpoint in case of error, which means we're getting a framework-generated 401 which the user application can't override to provide proper UI or even handling.\r\n\r\nWe should allow such error return paths, and I can see three options:\r\n\r\n- Invoke the callback endpoint, but provide a way to check for success or failure, via an API\r\n- Allow specifying an error callback endpoint (and provide access to the errors)\r\n- Throw a new type of exception that the user can handle specially, and otherwise it produces a 401\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
